  "text": "it, and building the resulting (smaller) kriging system while considering the anisotropy parameters constant within the neighborhood [CITATION_1] ). However, when applied to large seismic volumes, this method tends to be time consuming and sometimes introduces artifacts that are due to the fact that a collection of small local models are now considered instead of a big global one. This work aims at presenting an approach to geostatistical filtering that builds on the \"Stochastic Partial Differential Equations (SPDE) approach\" introduced by [CITATION_2] , and that allows filtering to be performed on a global setting while still addressing the limitations of the big n problem.",
